ear%2C%20IAS%20Jitendra%20conducted%20a%20survey%20in%20government%20schools%20and%20discovered%20that%20approximately%2048%20percent%20of%20students%20across%2021%20schools%20were%20anaemic.%20This%20was%20concerning%2C%20especially%20given%20that%20the%20Indian%20Government%20had%20been%20distributing%20Iron%20and%20Folic%20Acid%20(IFA)%20tablets%20through%20its%20Weekly%20Iron%20and%20Folic%20Acid%20Supplementation%20(WIFS)%20programme%20to%20combat%20the%20prevalence%20and%20severity%20of%20anaemia%20among%20adolescents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229669016977%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20tablets%20were%20being%20distributed%20every%20Wednesday%2C%20Jitendra%20observed%20that%20many%20children%20were%20hesitant%20to%20consume%20them%20due%20to%20misconceptions%20and%20lack%20of%20awareness.%20%E2%80%9CI%20learnt%20that%20there%20were%20incidences%20when%20children%20took%20IFA%20tablets%20and%20they%20fainted.%20Of%20course%2C%20their%20parents%20got%20worried%20and%20were%20suspicious%20of%20the%20free%20tablets%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20speaking%20to%20a%20few%20health%20providers%2C%20I%20learnt%20that%20these%20tablets%20should%20not%20be%20taken%20on%20an%20empty%20stomach.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IAS%20officer%20points%20out%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20many%20underprivileged%20households%2C%20breakfast%20is%20not%20a%20common%20practice%2C%20so%20most%20children%20rely%20on%20the%20mid-day%20meal%20provided%20at%20school.%20However%2C%20they%20were%20given%20Iron%20and%20Folic%20acid%20tablets%20during%20morning%20prayers%2C%20which%20put%20them%20at%20risk%20of%20fainting%20due%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20food%20beforehand.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20he%20introduced%20changes%20to%20the%20mid-da